==English==

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:AHD|AHD]]: lŏg
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /lɒg/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /lQg/

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# The trunk of a dead tree.
# The short form of a logbook, or a journal.
# (''Mathematics'') Short for [[logarithm]].

===Translations===
*Finnish: [[tukki]] (1), [[loki]] (2)
*Swedish: [[stock#Swedish|stock]] {{c}} (1), [[logg]] {{c}} (2), [[logaritm]] {{c}} (3)
*German: Logbuch (2), Logarithmus (3)

===Verb===
{{En-infl-reg-consonant|log||g}}

# To cut down trees.
# To make an entry in a log.

